				\begin{document}$${\rm{\tau }}=\frac{1}{2\pi {f}_{peak}}$$\end{document}where fpeak is the peak frequency at the minimum phase angle, 4.915 Hz for the ferro-based cell and 6.478 Hz for the glass-based cell. Both the increases in the Rct and τ lead to a reduced interface charge recombination in ferro-based cells.
